    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A top-down, multi-section dashboard SPA. The structure guides executives from the high-level recommendation to detailed, interactive data exploration. It starts with the 'Executive Summary' for a quick overview. Then, 'Cost & ROI' provides an interactive chart for TCO visualization. 'AI Showdown' offers a direct visual comparison of a key strategic pillar. 'Feature Deep-Dive' gives granular detail in a clear table. Finally, 'Migration Impact' visualizes the human and operational costs. This non-linear, thematic structure was chosen over a simple report layout to allow users to explore based on their priorities (e.g., a CFO might focus on Cost, a CTO on AI/Features), making the complex information more digestible and decision-oriented. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Annual Licensing Costs -> Goal: Compare TCO -> Viz: Interactive Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Toggles to add/remove MS Teams & Copilot costs -> Justification: Dynamically shows how add-ons dramatically alter the cost comparison, making the TCO argument tangible.
        - Report Info: ROI & Payback Figures -> Goal: Inform Financial Return -> Viz: Large Key Metric Cards -> Interaction: Static Display -> Justification: Highlights the most compelling financial outcomes for immediate impact.
        - Report Info: AI Feature Comparison -> Goal: Compare Strategic Capabilities -> Viz: Side-by-side card layout with icons -> Interaction: Static -> Justification: Clearly contrasts the 'included' vs. 'add-on' AI models, a critical strategic difference.
        - Report Info: Feature Matrix -> Goal: Organize Detailed Comparison -> Viz: HTML Table -> Interaction: Static -> Justification: Provides a clear, structured reference for functional parity.
        - Report Info: Migration Complexity -> Goal: Illustrate Operational Risk -> Viz: HTML/CSS Flow Diagram -> Interaction: Static -> Justification: Visually represents the disruptive steps of migration, making the abstract concept of 'migration cost' more concrete than a simple text list.
        - Library/Method: Chart.js for canvas-based charting. All other visuals are structured HTML with Tailwind CSS.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
